v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

32// The abstract syntax tree is an intermediate, light-weight
33// representation of the parsed JavaScript code suitable for
34// compilation to native code.
35
36// Nodes are allocated in a separate zone, which allows faster
37// allocation and constant-time deallocation of the entire syntax
38// tree.
39
40
41// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
42// Nodes of the abstract syntax tree. Only concrete classes are
43// enumerated here.
44
45#define DECLARATION_NODE_LIST(V) \
46 V(VariableDeclaration) \
47 V(FunctionDeclaration)
48
49#define ITERATION_NODE_LIST(V) \
50 V(DoWhileStatement) \
51 V(WhileStatement) \
52 V(ForStatement) \
53 V(ForInStatement) \
54 V(ForOfStatement)
55
56#define BREAKABLE_NODE_LIST(V) \
57 V(Block) \
58 V(SwitchStatement)
59
60#define STATEMENT_NODE_LIST(V) \
61 ITERATION_NODE_LIST(V) \
62 BREAKABLE_NODE_LIST(V) \
63 V(ExpressionStatement) \
64 V(EmptyStatement) \
65 V(SloppyBlockFunctionStatement) \
66 V(IfStatement) \
67 V(ContinueStatement) \
68 V(BreakStatement) \
69 V(ReturnStatement) \
70 V(WithStatement) \
71 V(TryCatchStatement) \
72 V(TryFinallyStatement) \
73 V(DebuggerStatement) \
74 V(InitializeClassMembersStatement) \
75 V(InitializeClassStaticElementsStatement) \
76 V(AutoAccessorGetterBody) \
77 V(AutoAccessorSetterBody)
78
79#define LITERAL_NODE_LIST(V) \
80 V(RegExpLiteral) \
81 V(ObjectLiteral) \
82 V(ArrayLiteral)
83
84#define EXPRESSION_NODE_LIST(V) \
85 LITERAL_NODE_LIST(V) \
86 V(Assignment) \
87 V(Await) \
88 V(BinaryOperation) \
89 V(NaryOperation) \
90 V(Call) \
91 V(SuperCallForwardArgs) \
92 V(CallNew) \
93 V(CallRuntime) \
94 V(ClassLiteral) \
95 V(CompareOperation) \
96 V(CompoundAssignment) \
97 V(ConditionalChain) \
98 V(Conditional) \
99 V(CountOperation) \
100 V(EmptyParentheses) \
101 V(FunctionLiteral) \
102 V(GetTemplateObject) \
103 V(ImportCallExpression) \
104 V(Literal) \
105 V(NativeFunctionLiteral) \
106 V(OptionalChain) \
107 V(Property) \
108 V(Spread) \
109 V(SuperCallReference) \
110 V(SuperPropertyReference) \
111 V(TemplateLiteral) \
112 V(ThisExpression) \
113 V(Throw) \
114 V(UnaryOperation) \
115 V(VariableProxy) \
116 V(Yield) \
117 V(YieldStar)

119#define FAILURE_NODE_LIST(V) V(FailureExpression)

122 DECLARATION_NODE_LIST(V) \
123 STATEMENT_NODE_LIST(V) \
124 EXPRESSION_NODE_LIST(V)

145class AstNode: public ZoneObject {
146 public:
147#define DECLARE_TYPE_ENUM(type) k##type,
148 enum NodeType : uint8_t {
149 AST_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_TYPE_ENUM) /* , */
150 FAILURE_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_TYPE_ENUM)
151 };
152#undef DECLARE_TYPE_ENUM
153
154 NodeType node_type() const { return NodeTypeField::decode(bit_field_); }
155 int position() const { return position_; }
156
157#ifdef DEBUG
158 void Print(Isolate* isolate);
159#endif // DEBUG
160
161 // Type testing & conversion functions overridden by concrete subclasses.
162#define DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS(type) \
163 V8_INLINE bool Is##type() const; \
164 V8_INLINE type* As##type(); \
165 V8_INLINE const type* As##type() const;
166 AST_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS)
167 FAILURE_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS)
168#undef DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS
169
170 IterationStatement* AsIterationStatement();
171 MaterializedLiteral* AsMaterializedLiteral();
172
173 private:
174 int position_;
175 using NodeTypeField = base::BitField<NodeType, 0, 6>;
176
177 protected:
178 uint32_t bit_field_;
179
180 template <class T, int size>
181 using NextBitField = NodeTypeField::Next<T, size>;
182
183 AstNode(int position, NodeType type)
184 : position_(position), bit_field_(NodeTypeField::encode(type)) {}
185};

194class Expression : public AstNode {
195 public:
196 enum Context {
197 // Not assigned a context yet, or else will not be visited during
198 // code generation.
199 kUninitialized,
200 // Evaluated for its side effects.
201 kEffect,
202 // Evaluated for its value (and side effects).
203 kValue,
204 // Evaluated for control flow (and side effects).
205 kTest
206 };
207
208 // True iff the expression is a valid reference expression.
209 bool IsValidReferenceExpression() const;
210
211 // True iff the expression is a private name.
212 bool IsPrivateName() const;
213
214 // Helpers for ToBoolean conversion.
215 bool ToBooleanIsTrue() const;
216 bool ToBooleanIsFalse() const;
217
218 // Symbols that cannot be parsed as array indices are considered property
219 // names. We do not treat symbols that can be array indexes as property
220 // names because [] for string objects is handled only by keyed ICs.
221 bool IsPropertyName() const;
222
223 // True iff the expression is a class or function expression without
224 // a syntactic name.
225 bool IsAnonymousFunctionDefinition() const;
226
227 // True iff the expression is a concise method definition.
228 bool IsConciseMethodDefinition() const;
229
230 // True iff the expression is an accessor function definition.
231 bool IsAccessorFunctionDefinition() const;
232
233 // True iff the expression is a literal represented as a smi.
234 bool IsSmiLiteral() const;
235
236 // True iff the expression is a literal represented as a number.
237 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool IsNumberLiteral() const;
238
239 // True iff the expression is a string literal.
240 bool IsStringLiteral() const;
241
242 // True iff the expression is a cons string literal.
243 bool IsConsStringLiteral() const;
244
245 // True iff the expression is the null literal.
246 bool IsNullLiteral() const;
247
248 bool IsBooleanLiteral() const;
249
250 // True iff the expression is the hole literal.
251 bool IsTheHoleLiteral() const;
252
253 // True if we can prove that the expression is the undefined literal. Note
254 // that this also checks for loads of the global "undefined" variable.
255 bool IsUndefinedLiteral() const;
256
257 // True if either null literal or undefined literal.
258 inline bool IsNullOrUndefinedLiteral() const {
259 return IsNullLiteral() || IsUndefinedLiteral();
260 }
261
262 // True if a literal and not null or undefined.
263 bool IsLiteralButNotNullOrUndefined() const;
264
265 bool IsCompileTimeValue();
266
267 bool IsPattern() {
268 static_assert(kObjectLiteral + 1 == kArrayLiteral);
269 return base::IsInRange(node_type(), kObjectLiteral, kArrayLiteral);
270 }
271
272 bool is_parenthesized() const {
273 return IsParenthesizedField::decode(bit_field_);
274 }
275
276 void mark_parenthesized() {
277 bit_field_ = IsParenthesizedField::update(bit_field_, true);
278 }
279
280 void clear_parenthesized() {
281 bit_field_ = IsParenthesizedField::update(bit_field_, false);
282 }
283
284 private:
285 using IsParenthesizedField = AstNode::NextBitField<bool, 1>;
286
287 protected:
288 Expression(int pos, NodeType type) : AstNode(pos, type) {
289 DCHECK(!is_parenthesized());
290 }
291
292 template <class T, int size>
293 using NextBitField = IsParenthesizedField::Next<T, size>;
294};

303// V8's notion of BreakableStatement does not correspond to the notion of
304// BreakableStatement in ECMAScript. In V8, the idea is that a
305// BreakableStatement is a statement that can be the target of a break
306// statement.
307//
308// Since we don't want to track a list of labels for all kinds of statements, we
309// only declare switchs, loops, and blocks as BreakableStatements. This means
310// that we implement breaks targeting other statement forms as breaks targeting
311// a substatement thereof. For instance, in "foo: if (b) { f(); break foo; }" we
312// pretend that foo is the label of the inner block. That's okay because one
313// can't observe the difference.
314// TODO(verwaest): Reconsider this optimization now that the tracking of labels
315// is done at runtime.
316class BreakableStatement : public Statement {
317 protected:
318 BreakableStatement(int position, NodeType type) : Statement(position, type) {}
319};
320
321class Block final : public BreakableStatement {
322 public:
323 ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements() { return &statements_; }
324 bool ignore_completion_value() const {
325 return IgnoreCompletionField::decode(bit_field_);
326 }
327 bool is_breakable() const { return IsBreakableField::decode(bit_field_); }
328 bool is_initialization_block_for_parameters() const {
329 return IsInitializationBlockForParametersField::decode(bit_field_);
330 }
331
332 Scope* scope() const { return scope_; }
333 void set_scope(Scope* scope) { scope_ = scope; }
334
335 void InitializeStatements(const ScopedPtrList<Statement>& statements,
336 Zone* zone) {
337 DCHECK_EQ(0, statements_.length());
338 statements_ = ZonePtrList<Statement>(statements.ToConstVector(), zone);
339 }
340
341 private:
342 friend class AstNodeFactory;
343 friend Zone;
344
345 ZonePtrList<Statement> statements_;
346 Scope* scope_;
347
348 using IgnoreCompletionField = BreakableStatement::NextBitField<bool, 1>;
349 using IsBreakableField = IgnoreCompletionField::Next<bool, 1>;
350 using IsInitializationBlockForParametersField =
351 IsBreakableField::Next<bool, 1>;
352
353 protected:
354 Block(Zone* zone, int capacity, bool ignore_completion_value,
355 bool is_breakable, bool is_initialization_block_for_parameters)
356 : BreakableStatement(kNoSourcePosition, kBlock),
357 statements_(capacity, zone),
358 scope_(nullptr) {
359 bit_field_ |= IgnoreCompletionField::encode(ignore_completion_value) |
360 IsBreakableField::encode(is_breakable) |
361 IsInitializationBlockForParametersField::encode(
362 is_initialization_block_for_parameters);
363 }
364
365 Block(bool ignore_completion_value, bool is_breakable,
366 bool is_initialization_block_for_parameters)
367 : Block(nullptr, 0, ignore_completion_value, is_breakable,
368 is_initialization_block_for_parameters) {}
369};

533// Shared class for for-in and for-of statements.
534class ForEachStatement : public IterationStatement {
535 public:
536 enum VisitMode {
537 ENUMERATE, // for (each in subject) body;
538 ITERATE // for (each of subject) body;
539 };
540
541 using IterationStatement::Initialize;
542
543 static const char* VisitModeString(VisitMode mode) {
544 return mode == ITERATE ? "for-of" : "for-in";
545 }
546

548 IterationStatement::Initialize(body);
549 each_ = each;
550 subject_ = subject;

554 Expression* subject() const { return subject_; }
555
556 protected:
557 friend class AstNodeFactory;
558 friend Zone;
559
560 ForEachStatement(int pos, NodeType type)
561 : IterationStatement(pos, type), each_(nullptr), subject_(nullptr) {}
562
563 Expression* each_;
564 Expression* subject_;
565};

642class ReturnStatement final : public JumpStatement {

741// If-statements always have non-null references to their then- and
742// else-parts. When parsing if-statements with no explicit else-part,
743// the parser implicitly creates an empty statement. Use the
744// HasThenStatement() and HasElseStatement() functions to check if a
745// given if-statement has a then- or an else-part containing code.
746class IfStatement final : public Statement {
747 public:
748 bool HasThenStatement() const { return !then_statement_->IsEmptyStatement(); }
749 bool HasElseStatement() const { return !else_statement_->IsEmptyStatement(); }
750
751 Expression* condition() const { return condition_; }
752 Statement* then_statement() const { return then_statement_; }
753 Statement* else_statement() const { return else_statement_; }
754
755 void set_then_statement(Statement* s) { then_statement_ = s; }
756 void set_else_statement(Statement* s) { else_statement_ = s; }
757
758 private:
759 friend class AstNodeFactory;
760 friend Zone;
761
762 IfStatement(Expression* condition, Statement* then_statement,
763 Statement* else_statement, int pos)
764 : Statement(pos, kIfStatement),
765 condition_(condition),
766 then_statement_(then_statement),
767 else_statement_(else_statement) {}
768
769 Expression* condition_;
770 Statement* then_statement_;
771 Statement* else_statement_;
772};

789class TryCatchStatement final : public TryStatement {
790 public:
791 Scope* scope() { return scope_; }
792 Block* catch_block() const { return catch_block_; }
793 void set_catch_block(Block* b) { catch_block_ = b; }
794
795 // Prediction of whether exceptions thrown into the handler for this try block
796 // will be caught.
797 //
798 // BytecodeGenerator tracks the state of catch prediction, which can change
799 // with each TryCatchStatement encountered. The tracked catch prediction is
800 // later compiled into the code's handler table. The runtime uses this
801 // information to implement a feature that notifies the debugger when an
802 // uncaught exception is thrown, _before_ the exception propagates to the top.
803 //
804 // If this try/catch statement is meant to rethrow (HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT),
805 // the catch prediction value is set to the same value as the surrounding
806 // catch prediction.
807 //
808 // Since it's generally undecidable whether an exception will be caught, our
809 // prediction is only an approximation.
810 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
811 inline HandlerTable::CatchPrediction GetCatchPrediction(
812 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction) const {
813 if (catch_prediction_ == HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT) {
814 return outer_catch_prediction;
815 }
816 return catch_prediction_;
817 }
818
819 // Indicates whether or not code should be generated to clear the pending
820 // exception. The exception is cleared for cases where the exception
821 // is not guaranteed to be rethrown, indicated by the value
822 // HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT. If both the current and surrounding catch handler's
823 // are predicted uncaught, the exception is not cleared.
824 //
825 // If this handler is not going to simply rethrow the exception, this method
826 // indicates that the isolate's exception message should be cleared
827 // before executing the catch_block.
828 // In the normal use case, this flag is always on because the message object
829 // is not needed anymore when entering the catch block and should not be
830 // kept alive.
831 // The use case where the flag is off is when the catch block is guaranteed
832 // to rethrow the caught exception (using %ReThrow), which reuses the
833 // pending message instead of generating a new one.
834 // (When the catch block doesn't rethrow but is guaranteed to perform an
835 // ordinary throw, not clearing the old message is safe but not very
836 // useful.)
837 //
838 // For scripts in repl mode there is exactly one catch block with
839 // UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT prediction. This catch block needs to preserve
840 // the exception so it can be re-used later by the inspector.
841 inline bool ShouldClearException(
842 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction outer_catch_prediction) const {
843 if (catch_prediction_ == HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT_ASYNC_AWAIT) {
844 DCHECK_EQ(outer_catch_prediction, HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT);
845 return false;
846 }
847
848 return catch_prediction_ != HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT ||
849 outer_catch_prediction != HandlerTable::UNCAUGHT;
850 }
851
852 bool is_try_catch_for_async() {
853 return catch_prediction_ == HandlerTable::ASYNC_AWAIT;
854 }
855
856 private:
857 friend class AstNodeFactory;
858 friend Zone;
859
860 TryCatchStatement(Block* try_block, Scope* scope, Block* catch_block,
861 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction, int pos)
862 : TryStatement(try_block, pos, kTryCatchStatement),
863 scope_(scope),
864 catch_block_(catch_block),
865 catch_prediction_(catch_prediction) {}
866
867 Scope* scope_;
868 Block* catch_block_;
869 HandlerTable::CatchPrediction catch_prediction_;
870};

942class Literal final : public Expression {
943 public:
944 enum Type {
945 kSmi,
946 kHeapNumber,
947 kBigInt,
948 kString,
949 kConsString,
950 kBoolean,
951 kUndefined,
952 kNull,
953 kTheHole,
954 };
955
956 Type type() const { return TypeField::decode(bit_field_); }
957
958 // Returns true if literal represents a property name (i.e. cannot be parsed
959 // as array indices).
960 bool IsPropertyName() const;
961
962 // Returns true if literal represents an array index.
963 // Note, that in general the following statement is not true:
964 // key->IsPropertyName() != key->AsArrayIndex(...)
965 // but for non-computed LiteralProperty properties the following is true:
966 // property->key()->IsPropertyName() != property->key()->AsArrayIndex(...)
967 bool AsArrayIndex(uint32_t* index) const;
968
969 const AstRawString* AsRawPropertyName() {
970 DCHECK(IsPropertyName());
971 return string_;
972 }
973
974 Tagged<Smi> AsSmiLiteral() const {
975 DCHECK_EQ(kSmi, type());
976 return Smi::FromInt(smi_);
977 }
978
979 bool AsBooleanLiteral() const {
980 DCHECK_EQ(kBoolean, type());
981 return boolean_;
982 }
983
984 // Returns true if literal represents a Number.
985 bool IsNumber() const { return type() == kHeapNumber || type() == kSmi; }
986 double AsNumber() const {
987 DCHECK(IsNumber());
988 switch (type()) {
989 case kSmi:
990 return smi_;
991 case kHeapNumber:
992 return number_;
993 default:
994 UNREACHABLE();
995 }
996 }
997
998 AstBigInt AsBigInt() const {
999 DCHECK_EQ(type(), kBigInt);
1000 return bigint_;
1001 }
1002
1003 bool IsRawString() const { return type() == kString; }
1004 const AstRawString* AsRawString() {
1005 DCHECK_EQ(type(), kString);
1006 return string_;
1007 }
1008
1009 bool IsConsString() const { return type() == kConsString; }
1010 AstConsString* AsConsString() {
1011 DCHECK_EQ(type(), kConsString);
1012 return cons_string_;
1013 }
1014
1015 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool ToBooleanIsTrue() const;
1016 bool ToBooleanIsFalse() const { return !ToBooleanIsTrue(); }
1017
1018 bool ToUint32(uint32_t* value) const;
1019
1020 // Returns an appropriate Object representing this Literal, allocating
1021 // a heap object if needed.
1022 template <typename IsolateT>
1023 Handle<Object> BuildValue(IsolateT* isolate) const;
1024
1025 // Support for using Literal as a HashMap key. NOTE: Currently, this works
1026 // only for string and number literals!
1027 uint32_t Hash();
1028 static bool Match(void* literal1, void* literal2);
1029
1030 private:
1031 friend class AstNodeFactory;
1032 friend Zone;
1033
1034 using TypeField = Expression::NextBitField<Type, 4>;
1035
1036 Literal(int smi, int position) : Expression(position, kLiteral), smi_(smi) {
1037 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kSmi);
1038 }
1039
1040 Literal(double number, int position)
1041 : Expression(position, kLiteral), number_(number) {
1042 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kHeapNumber);
1043 }
1044
1045 Literal(AstBigInt bigint, int position)
1046 : Expression(position, kLiteral), bigint_(bigint) {
1047 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kBigInt);
1048 }
1049
1050 Literal(const AstRawString* string, int position)
1051 : Expression(position, kLiteral), string_(string) {
1052 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kString);
1053 }
1054
1055 Literal(AstConsString* string, int position)
1056 : Expression(position, kLiteral), cons_string_(string) {
1057 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kConsString);
1058 }
1059
1060 Literal(bool boolean, int position)
1061 : Expression(position, kLiteral), boolean_(boolean) {
1062 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, kBoolean);
1063 }
1064
1065 Literal(Type type, int position) : Expression(position, kLiteral) {
1066 DCHECK(type == kNull || type == kUndefined || type == kTheHole);
1067 bit_field_ = TypeField::update(bit_field_, type);
1068 }
1069
1070 union {
1071 const AstRawString* string_;
1072 AstConsString* cons_string_;
1073 int smi_;
1074 double number_;
1075 AstBigInt bigint_;
1076 bool boolean_;
1077 };
1078};

1134// Base class for build literal boilerplate, providing common code for handling
1135// nested subliterals.
1136class LiteralBoilerplateBuilder {
1137 public:
1138 enum DepthKind { kUninitialized, kShallow, kNotShallow };
1139
1140 static constexpr int kDepthKindBits = 2;
1141 static_assert((1 << kDepthKindBits) > kNotShallow);
1142
1143 bool is_initialized() const {
1144 return kUninitialized != DepthField::decode(bit_field_);
1145 }
1146 DepthKind depth() const {
1147 DCHECK(is_initialized());
1148 return DepthField::decode(bit_field_);
1149 }
1150
1151 // If the expression is a literal, return the literal value;
1152 // if the expression is a materialized literal and is_simple
1153 // then return an Array or Object Boilerplate Description
1154 // Otherwise, return undefined literal as the placeholder
1155 // in the object literal boilerplate.
1156 template <typename IsolateT>
1157 static Handle<Object> GetBoilerplateValue(Expression* expression,
1158 IsolateT* isolate);
1159
1160 bool is_shallow() const { return depth() == kShallow; }
1161 bool needs_initial_allocation_site() const {
1162 return NeedsInitialAllocationSiteField::decode(bit_field_);
1163 }
1164
1165 int ComputeFlags(bool disable_mementos = false) const {
1166 int flags = AggregateLiteral::kNoFlags;
1167 if (is_shallow()) flags |= AggregateLiteral::kIsShallow;
1168 if (disable_mementos) flags |= AggregateLiteral::kDisableMementos;
1169 if (needs_initial_allocation_site())
1170 flags |= AggregateLiteral::kNeedsInitialAllocationSite;
1171 return flags;
1172 }
1173
1174 // An AggregateLiteral is simple if the values consist of only
1175 // constants and simple object and array literals.
1176 bool is_simple() const { return IsSimpleField::decode(bit_field_); }
1177
1178 ElementsKind boilerplate_descriptor_kind() const {
1179 return BoilerplateDescriptorKindField::decode(bit_field_);
1180 }
1181
1182 private:
1183 // we actually only care three conditions for depth
1184 // - depth == kUninitialized, DCHECK(!is_initialized())
1185 // - depth == kShallow, which means depth = 1
1186 // - depth == kNotShallow, which means depth > 1
1187 using DepthField = base::BitField<DepthKind, 0, kDepthKindBits>;
1188 using NeedsInitialAllocationSiteField = DepthField::Next<bool, 1>;
1189 using IsSimpleField = NeedsInitialAllocationSiteField::Next<bool, 1>;
1190 using BoilerplateDescriptorKindField =
1191 IsSimpleField::Next<ElementsKind, kFastElementsKindBits>;
1192
1193 protected:
1194 uint32_t bit_field_;
1195
1196 LiteralBoilerplateBuilder() {
1197 bit_field_ =
1198 DepthField::encode(kUninitialized) |
1199 NeedsInitialAllocationSiteField::encode(false) |
1200 IsSimpleField::encode(false) |
1201 BoilerplateDescriptorKindField::encode(FIRST_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND);
1202 }
1203
1204 void set_is_simple(bool is_simple) {
1205 bit_field_ = IsSimpleField::update(bit_field_, is_simple);
1206 }
1207
1208 void set_boilerplate_descriptor_kind(ElementsKind kind) {
1209 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(kind));
1210 bit_field_ = BoilerplateDescriptorKindField::update(bit_field_, kind);
1211 }
1212
1213 void set_depth(DepthKind depth) {
1214 DCHECK(!is_initialized());
1215 bit_field_ = DepthField::update(bit_field_, depth);
1216 }
1217
1218 void set_needs_initial_allocation_site(bool required) {
1219 bit_field_ = NeedsInitialAllocationSiteField::update(bit_field_, required);
1220 }
1221
1222 // Populate the depth field and any flags the literal builder has
1223 static void InitDepthAndFlags(MaterializedLiteral* expr);
1224
1225 // Populate the constant properties/elements fixed array.
1226 template <typename IsolateT>
1227 void BuildConstants(IsolateT* isolate, MaterializedLiteral* expr);
1228
1229 template <class T, int size>
1230 using NextBitField = BoilerplateDescriptorKindField::Next<T, size>;
1231};

1292// class for build object boilerplate
1293class ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder final : public LiteralBoilerplateBuilder {
1294 public:
1295 using Property = ObjectLiteralProperty;
1296
1297 ObjectLiteralBoilerplateBuilder(ZoneList<Property*>* properties,
1298 uint32_t boilerplate_properties,
1299 bool has_rest_property)
1300 : properties_(properties),
1301 boilerplate_properties_(boilerplate_properties) {
1302 bit_field_ |= HasElementsField::encode(false) |
1303 HasRestPropertyField::encode(has_rest_property) |
1304 FastElementsField::encode(false) |
1305 HasNullPrototypeField::encode(false);
1306 }
1307 Handle<ObjectBoilerplateDescription> boilerplate_description() const {
1308 DCHECK(!boilerplate_description_.is_null());
1309 return boilerplate_description_;
1310 }
1311 // Determines whether the {CreateShallowArrayLiteral} builtin can be used.
1312 bool IsFastCloningSupported() const;
1313
1314 int properties_count() const { return boilerplate_properties_; }
1315 const ZonePtrList<Property>* properties() const { return properties_; }
1316 bool has_elements() const { return HasElementsField::decode(bit_field_); }
1317 bool has_rest_property() const {
1318 return HasRestPropertyField::decode(bit_field_);
1319 }
1320 bool fast_elements() const { return FastElementsField::decode(bit_field_); }
1321 bool has_null_prototype() const {
1322 return HasNullPrototypeField::decode(bit_field_);
1323 }
1324
1325 // Populate the boilerplate description.
1326 template <typename IsolateT>
1327 void BuildBoilerplateDescription(IsolateT* isolate);
1328
1329 // Get the boilerplate description, populating it if necessary.
1330 template <typename IsolateT>
1331 Handle<ObjectBoilerplateDescription> GetOrBuildBoilerplateDescription(
1332 IsolateT* isolate) {
1333 if (boilerplate_description_.is_null()) {
1334 BuildBoilerplateDescription(isolate);
1335 }
1336 return boilerplate_description_;
1337 }
1338
1339 bool is_empty() const {
1340 DCHECK(is_initialized());
1341 return !has_elements() && properties_count() == 0 &&
1342 properties()->length() == 0;
1343 }
1344 // Assemble bitfield of flags for the CreateObjectLiteral helper.
1345 int ComputeFlags(bool disable_mementos = false) const;
1346
1347 bool IsEmptyObjectLiteral() const {
1348 return is_empty() && !has_null_prototype();
1349 }
1350
1351 int EncodeLiteralType();
1352
1353 // Populate the depth field and flags, returns the depth.
1354 void InitDepthAndFlags();
1355
1356 private:
1357 void InitFlagsForPendingNullPrototype(int i);
1358
1359 void set_has_elements(bool has_elements) {
1360 bit_field_ = HasElementsField::update(bit_field_, has_elements);
1361 }
1362 void set_fast_elements(bool fast_elements) {
1363 bit_field_ = FastElementsField::update(bit_field_, fast_elements);
1364 }
1365 void set_has_null_protoype(bool has_null_prototype) {
1366 bit_field_ = HasNullPrototypeField::update(bit_field_, has_null_prototype);
1367 }
1368 ZoneList<Property*>* properties_;
1369 uint32_t boilerplate_properties_;
1370 IndirectHandle<ObjectBoilerplateDescription> boilerplate_description_;
1371
1372 using HasElementsField = LiteralBoilerplateBuilder::NextBitField<bool, 1>;
1373 using HasRestPropertyField = HasElementsField::Next<bool, 1>;
1374 using FastElementsField = HasRestPropertyField::Next<bool, 1>;
1375 using HasNullPrototypeField = FastElementsField::Next<bool, 1>;
1376};

1497class VariableProxy final : public Expression {
1498 public:
1499 bool IsValidReferenceExpression() const { return !is_new_target(); }
1500
1501 Handle<String> name() const { return raw_name()->string(); }
1502 const AstRawString* raw_name() const {
1503 return is_resolved() ? var_->raw_name() : raw_name_;
1504 }
1505
1506 Variable* var() const {
1507 DCHECK(is_resolved());
1508 return var_;
1509 }
1510 void set_var(Variable* v) {
1511 DCHECK(!is_resolved());
1512 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(v);
1513 var_ = v;
1514 }
1515
1516 Scanner::Location location() {
1517 return Scanner::Location(position(), position() + raw_name()->length());
1518 }
1519
1520 bool is_assigned() const { return IsAssignedField::decode(bit_field_); }
1521 void set_is_assigned() {
1522 bit_field_ = IsAssignedField::update(bit_field_, true);
1523 if (is_resolved()) {
1524 var()->SetMaybeAssigned();
1525 }
1526 }
1527 void clear_is_assigned() {
1528 bit_field_ = IsAssignedField::update(bit_field_, false);
1529 }
1530
1531 bool is_resolved() const { return IsResolvedField::decode(bit_field_); }
1532 void set_is_resolved() {
1533 bit_field_ = IsResolvedField::update(bit_field_, true);
1534 }
1535
1536 bool is_new_target() const { return IsNewTargetField::decode(bit_field_); }
1537 void set_is_new_target() {
1538 bit_field_ = IsNewTargetField::update(bit_field_, true);
1539 }
1540
1541 HoleCheckMode hole_check_mode() const {
1542 HoleCheckMode mode = HoleCheckModeField::decode(bit_field_);
1543 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == HoleCheckMode::kRequired,
1544 var()->binding_needs_init() ||
1545 var()->local_if_not_shadowed()->binding_needs_init());
1546 return mode;
1547 }
1548 void set_needs_hole_check() {
1549 bit_field_ =
1550 HoleCheckModeField::update(bit_field_, HoleCheckMode::kRequired);
1551 }
1552
1553 bool IsPrivateName() const { return raw_name()->IsPrivateName(); }
1554
1555 // Bind this proxy to the variable var.
1556 void BindTo(Variable* var);
1557
1558 V8_INLINE VariableProxy* next_unresolved() { return next_unresolved_; }
1559 V8_INLINE bool is_removed_from_unresolved() const {
1560 return IsRemovedFromUnresolvedField::decode(bit_field_);
1561 }
1562
1563 void mark_removed_from_unresolved() {
1564 bit_field_ = IsRemovedFromUnresolvedField::update(bit_field_, true);
1565 }
1566
1567 bool is_home_object() const { return IsHomeObjectField::decode(bit_field_); }
1568
1569 void set_is_home_object() {
1570 bit_field_ = IsHomeObjectField::update(bit_field_, true);
1571 }
1572
1573 // Provides filtered access to the unresolved variable proxy threaded list.
1574 struct UnresolvedNext {
1575 static VariableProxy** filter(VariableProxy** t) {
1576 VariableProxy** n = t;
1577 // Skip over possibly removed values.
1578 while (*n != nullptr && (*n)->is_removed_from_unresolved()) {
1579 n = (*n)->next();
1580 }
1581 return n;
1582 }
1583
1584 static VariableProxy** start(VariableProxy** head) { return filter(head); }
1585
1586 static VariableProxy** next(VariableProxy* t) { return filter(t->next()); }
1587 };
1588
1589 private:
1590 friend class AstNodeFactory;
1591 friend Zone;
1592
1593 VariableProxy(Variable* var, int start_position);
1594
1595 VariableProxy(const AstRawString* name, VariableKind variable_kind,
1596 int start_position)
1597 : Expression(start_position, kVariableProxy),
1598 raw_name_(name),
1599 next_unresolved_(nullptr) {
1600 DCHECK_NE(THIS_VARIABLE, variable_kind);
1601 bit_field_ |= IsAssignedField::encode(false) |
1602 IsResolvedField::encode(false) |
1603 IsRemovedFromUnresolvedField::encode(false) |
1604 IsHomeObjectField::encode(false) |
1605 HoleCheckModeField::encode(HoleCheckMode::kElided);
1606 }
1607
1608 explicit VariableProxy(const VariableProxy* copy_from);
1609
1610 using IsAssignedField = Expression::NextBitField<bool, 1>;
1611 using IsResolvedField = IsAssignedField::Next<bool, 1>;
1612 using IsRemovedFromUnresolvedField = IsResolvedField::Next<bool, 1>;
1613 using IsNewTargetField = IsRemovedFromUnresolvedField::Next<bool, 1>;
1614 using IsHomeObjectField = IsNewTargetField::Next<bool, 1>;
1615 using HoleCheckModeField = IsHomeObjectField::Next<HoleCheckMode, 1>;
1616
1617 union {
1618 const AstRawString* raw_name_; // if !is_resolved_
1619 Variable* var_; // if is_resolved_
1620 };
1621
1622 V8_INLINE VariableProxy** next() { return &next_unresolved_; }
1623 VariableProxy* next_unresolved_;
1624
1625 friend base::ThreadedListTraits<VariableProxy>;
1626};

1643// Assignments to a property will use one of several types of property access.
1644// Otherwise, the assignment is to a non-property (a global, a local slot, a
1645// parameter slot, or a destructuring pattern).
1646enum AssignType {
1647 NON_PROPERTY, // destructuring
1648 NAMED_PROPERTY, // obj.key
1649 KEYED_PROPERTY, // obj[key] and obj.#key when #key is a private field
1650 NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY, // super.key
1651 KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY, // super[key]
1652 PRIVATE_METHOD, // obj.#key: #key is a private method
1653 PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY, // obj.#key: #key only has a getter defined
1654 PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY, // obj.#key: #key only has a setter defined
1655 PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER, // obj.#key: #key has both accessors defined
1656 PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC, // obj.#key: #key is private that requries dynamic
1657 // lookup in debug-evaluate.
1658};
1659
1660class Property final : public Expression {
1661 public:
1662 bool is_optional_chain_link() const {
1663 return IsOptionalChainLinkField::decode(bit_field_);
1664 }
1665
1666 bool IsValidReferenceExpression() const { return true; }
1667
1668 Expression* obj() const { return obj_; }
1669 Expression* key() const { return key_; }
1670
1671 bool IsSuperAccess() { return obj()->IsSuperPropertyReference(); }
1672 bool IsPrivateReference() const { return key()->IsPrivateName(); }
1673
1674 // Returns the properties assign type.
1675 static AssignType GetAssignType(Property* property) {
1676 if (property == nullptr) return NON_PROPERTY;
1677 if (property->IsPrivateReference()) {
1678 DCHECK(!property->IsSuperAccess());
1679 VariableProxy* proxy = property->key()->AsVariableProxy();
1680 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(proxy);
1681 Variable* var = proxy->var();
1682
1683 switch (var->mode()) {
1684 case VariableMode::kPrivateMethod:
1685 return PRIVATE_METHOD;
1686 case VariableMode::kConst:
1687 return KEYED_PROPERTY; // Use KEYED_PROPERTY for private fields.
1688 case VariableMode::kPrivateGetterOnly:
1689 return PRIVATE_GETTER_ONLY;
1690 case VariableMode::kPrivateSetterOnly:
1691 return PRIVATE_SETTER_ONLY;
1692 case VariableMode::kPrivateGetterAndSetter:
1693 return PRIVATE_GETTER_AND_SETTER;
1694 case VariableMode::kDynamic:
1695 // From debug-evaluate.
1696 return PRIVATE_DEBUG_DYNAMIC;
1697 default:
1698 UNREACHABLE();
1699 }
1700 }
1701 bool super_access = property->IsSuperAccess();
1702 return (property->key()->IsPropertyName())
1703 ? (super_access ? NAMED_SUPER_PROPERTY : NAMED_PROPERTY)
1704 : (super_access ? KEYED_SUPER_PROPERTY : KEYED_PROPERTY);
1705 }
1706
1707 private:
1708 friend class AstNodeFactory;
1709 friend Zone;
1710
1711 Property(Expression* obj, Expression* key, int pos, bool optional_chain)
1712 : Expression(pos, kProperty), obj_(obj), key_(key) {
1713 bit_field_ |= IsOptionalChainLinkField::encode(optional_chain);
1714 }
1715
1716 using IsOptionalChainLinkField = Expression::NextBitField<bool, 1>;
1717
1718 Expression* obj_;
1719 Expression* key_;
1720};

1961 // Nary operations store the first (lhs) child expression inline, and the
1962 // child expressions (rhs of each op) are stored out-of-line, along with
1963 // their operation's position. Note that the Nary operation expression's
1964 // position has no meaning.
1965 //
1966 // So an nary add:
1967 //
1968 // expr + expr + expr + ...
1969 //
1970 // is stored as:
1971 //
1972 // (expr) [(+ expr), (+ expr), ...]
1973 // '-.--' '-----------.-----------'
1974 // first subsequent entry list
1975
1976 Expression* first_;
1977
1978 struct NaryOperationEntry {
1979 Expression* expression;
1980 int op_position;
1981 NaryOperationEntry(Expression* e, int pos)
1982 : expression(e), op_position(pos) {}
1983 };
1984 ZoneVector<NaryOperationEntry> subsequent_;
1985
1986 using OperatorField = Expression::NextBitField<Token::Value, 7>;
1987};

2063class ConditionalChain : public Expression {
2064 public:
2065 Expression* condition_at(size_t index) const {
2066 return conditional_chain_entries_[index].condition;
2067 }
2068 Expression* then_expression_at(size_t index) const {
2069 return conditional_chain_entries_[index].then_expression;
2070 }
2071 int condition_position_at(size_t index) const {
2072 return conditional_chain_entries_[index].condition_position;
2073 }
2074 size_t conditional_chain_length() const {
2075 return conditional_chain_entries_.size();
2076 }
2077 Expression* else_expression() const { return else_expression_; }
2078 void set_else_expression(Expression* s) { else_expression_ = s; }
2079
2080 void AddChainEntry(Expression* cond, Expression* then, int pos) {
2081 conditional_chain_entries_.emplace_back(cond, then, pos);
2082 }
2083
2084 private:
2085 friend class AstNodeFactory;
2086 friend Zone;
2087
2088 ConditionalChain(Zone* zone, size_t initial_size, int pos)
2089 : Expression(pos, kConditionalChain),
2090 conditional_chain_entries_(zone),
2091 else_expression_(nullptr) {
2092 conditional_chain_entries_.reserve(initial_size);
2093 }
2094
2095 // Conditional Chain Expression stores the conditional chain entries out of
2096 // line, along with their operation's position. The else expression is stored
2097 // inline. This Expression is reserved for ternary operations that have more
2098 // than one conditional chain entry. For ternary operations with only one
2099 // conditional chain entry, the Conditional Expression is used instead.
2100 //
2101 // So an conditional chain:
2102 //
2103 // cond ? then : cond ? then : cond ? then : else
2104 //
2105 // is stored as:
2106 //
2107 // [(cond, then), (cond, then),...] else
2108 // '-----------------------------' '----'
2109 // conditional chain entries else
2110 //
2111 // Example:
2112 //
2113 // Expression: v1 == 1 ? "a" : v2 == 2 ? "b" : "c"
2114 //
2115 // conditionat_chain_entries_: [(v1 == 1, "a", 0), (v2 == 2, "b", 14)]
2116 // else_expression_: "c"
2117 //
2118 // Example of a _not_ expected expression (only one chain entry):
2119 //
2120 // Expression: v1 == 1 ? "a" : "b"
2121 //
2122
2123 struct ConditionalChainEntry {
2124 Expression* condition;
2125 Expression* then_expression;
2126 int condition_position;
2127 ConditionalChainEntry(Expression* cond, Expression* then, int pos)
2128 : condition(cond), then_expression(then), condition_position(pos) {}
2129 };
2130 ZoneVector<ConditionalChainEntry> conditional_chain_entries_;
2131 Expression* else_expression_;
2132};
2133

2205// There are several types of Suspend node:
2206//
2207// Yield
2208// YieldStar
2209// Await
2210//
2211// Our Yield is different from the JS yield in that it "returns" its argument as
2212// is, without wrapping it in an iterator result object. Such wrapping, if
2213// desired, must be done beforehand (see the parser).
2214class Suspend : public Expression {
2215 public:
2216 // With {kNoControl}, the {Suspend} behaves like yield, except that it never
2217 // throws and never causes the current generator to return. This is used to
2218 // desugar yield*.
2219 // TODO(caitp): remove once yield* desugaring for async generators is handled
2220 // in BytecodeGenerator.
2221 enum OnAbruptResume { kOnExceptionThrow, kNoControl };
2222
2223 Expression* expression() const { return expression_; }
2224 OnAbruptResume on_abrupt_resume() const {
2225 return OnAbruptResumeField::decode(bit_field_);
2226 }
2227
2228 private:
2229 friend class AstNodeFactory;
2230 friend Zone;
2231 friend class Yield;
2232 friend class YieldStar;
2233 friend class Await;
2234
2235 Suspend(NodeType node_type, Expression* expression, int pos,
2236 OnAbruptResume on_abrupt_resume)
2237 : Expression(pos, node_type), expression_(expression) {
2238 bit_field_ |= OnAbruptResumeField::encode(on_abrupt_resume);
2239 }
2240
2241 Expression* expression_;
2242
2243 using OnAbruptResumeField = Expression::NextBitField<OnAbruptResume, 1>;
2244};

2287class FunctionLiteral final : public Expression {
2288 public:
2289 enum ParameterFlag : uint8_t {
2290 kNoDuplicateParameters,
2291 kHasDuplicateParameters
2292 };
2293 enum EagerCompileHint : uint8_t { kShouldEagerCompile, kShouldLazyCompile };
2294
2295 // Empty handle means that the function does not have a shared name (i.e.
2296 // the name will be set dynamically after creation of the function closure).
2297 template <typename IsolateT>
2298 MaybeHandle<String> GetName(IsolateT* isolate) const {
2299 return raw_name_ ? raw_name_->AllocateFlat(isolate) : MaybeHandle<String>();
2300 }
2301 bool has_shared_name() const { return raw_name_ != nullptr; }
2302 const AstConsString* raw_name() const { return raw_name_; }
2303 void set_raw_name(const AstConsString* name) { raw_name_ = name; }
2304 DeclarationScope* scope() const { return scope_; }
2305 ZonePtrList<Statement>* body() { return &body_; }
2306 void set_function_token_position(int pos) { function_token_position_ = pos; }
2307 int function_token_position() const { return function_token_position_; }
2308 int start_position() const;
2309 int end_position() const;
2310 bool is_anonymous_expression() const {
2311 return syntax_kind() == FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression;
2312 }
2313
2314 bool is_toplevel() const {
2315 return function_literal_id() == kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel;
2316 }
2317 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE LanguageMode language_mode() const;
2318
2319 void add_expected_properties(int number_properties) {
2320 expected_property_count_ += number_properties;
2321 }
2322 int expected_property_count() { return expected_property_count_; }
2323 int parameter_count() { return parameter_count_; }
2324 int function_length() { return function_length_; }
2325
2326 bool AllowsLazyCompilation();
2327
2328 bool CanSuspend() {
2329 if (suspend_count() > 0) {
2330 DCHECK(IsResumableFunction(kind()));
2331 return true;
2332 }
2333 return false;
2334 }
2335
2336 // Returns either name or inferred name as a cstring.
2337 std::unique_ptr<char[]> GetDebugName() const;
2338
2339 Handle<String> GetInferredName(Isolate* isolate);
2340 Handle<String> GetInferredName(LocalIsolate* isolate) const {
2341 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(raw_inferred_name_);
2342 return raw_inferred_name_->GetString(isolate);
2343 }
2344
2345 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_function_info() const {
2346 return shared_function_info_;
2347 }
2348 void set_shared_function_info(
2349 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_function_info);
2350
2351 const AstConsString* raw_inferred_name() { return raw_inferred_name_; }
2352 // This should only be called if we don't have a shared function info yet.
2353 void set_raw_inferred_name(AstConsString* raw_inferred_name);
2354
2355 bool pretenure() const { return Pretenure::decode(bit_field_); }
2356 void set_pretenure() { bit_field_ = Pretenure::update(bit_field_, true); }
2357
2358 bool has_duplicate_parameters() const {
2359 // Not valid for lazy functions.
2360 DCHECK(ShouldEagerCompile());
2361 return HasDuplicateParameters::decode(bit_field_);
2362 }
2363
2364 bool should_parallel_compile() const {
2365 return ShouldParallelCompileField::decode(bit_field_);
2366 }
2367 void set_should_parallel_compile() {
2368 bit_field_ = ShouldParallelCompileField::update(bit_field_, true);
2369 }
2370
2371 // This is used as a heuristic on when to eagerly compile a function
2372 // literal. We consider the following constructs as hints that the
2373 // function will be called immediately:
2374 // - (function() { ... })();
2375 // - var x = function() { ... }();
2376 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool ShouldEagerCompile() const;
2377 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void SetShouldEagerCompile();
2378
2379 FunctionSyntaxKind syntax_kind() const {
2380 return FunctionSyntaxKindBits::decode(bit_field_);
2381 }
2382 FunctionKind kind() const;
2383
2384 bool IsAnonymousFunctionDefinition() const {
2385 return is_anonymous_expression();
2386 }
2387
2388 int suspend_count() { return suspend_count_; }
2389 void set_suspend_count(int suspend_count) { suspend_count_ = suspend_count; }
2390
2391 int return_position() {
2392 return std::max(
2393 start_position(),
2394 end_position() - (HasBracesField::decode(bit_field_) ? 1 : 0));
2395 }
2396
2397 int function_literal_id() const { return function_literal_id_; }

2399 function_literal_id_ = function_literal_id;
2400 }
2401
2402 void set_requires_instance_members_initializer(bool value) {
2403 bit_field_ = RequiresInstanceMembersInitializer::update(bit_field_, value);
2404 }
2405 bool requires_instance_members_initializer() const {
2406 return RequiresInstanceMembersInitializer::decode(bit_field_);
2407 }
2408

2410 bit_field_ =
2411 HasStaticPrivateMethodsOrAccessorsField::update(bit_field_, value);
2412 }
2413 bool has_static_private_methods_or_accessors() const {
2414 return HasStaticPrivateMethodsOrAccessorsField::decode(bit_field_);
2415 }
2416
2417 void set_class_scope_has_private_brand(bool value);
2418 bool class_scope_has_private_brand() const;
2419
2420 bool private_name_lookup_skips_outer_class() const;
2421
2422 ProducedPreparseData* produced_preparse_data() const {
2423 return produced_preparse_data_;
2424 }
2425
2426 private:
2427 friend class AstNodeFactory;
2428 friend Zone;
2429
2430 FunctionLiteral(Zone* zone, const AstConsString* name,
2431 AstValueFactory* ast_value_factory, DeclarationScope* scope,
2432 const ScopedPtrList<Statement>& body,
2433 int expected_property_count, int parameter_count,
2434 int function_length, FunctionSyntaxKind function_syntax_kind,
2435 ParameterFlag has_duplicate_parameters,
2436 EagerCompileHint eager_compile_hint, int position,
2437 bool has_braces, int function_literal_id,
2438 ProducedPreparseData* produced_preparse_data = nullptr)
2439 : Expression(position, kFunctionLiteral),
2440 expected_property_count_(expected_property_count),
2441 parameter_count_(parameter_count),
2442 function_length_(function_length),
2443 function_token_position_(kNoSourcePosition),
2444 suspend_count_(0),
2445 function_literal_id_(function_literal_id),
2446 raw_name_(name),
2447 scope_(scope),
2448 body_(body.ToConstVector(), zone),
2449 raw_inferred_name_(ast_value_factory->empty_cons_string()),
2450 produced_preparse_data_(produced_preparse_data) {
2451 bit_field_ |= FunctionSyntaxKindBits::encode(function_syntax_kind) |
2452 Pretenure::encode(false) |
2453 HasDuplicateParameters::encode(has_duplicate_parameters ==
2454 kHasDuplicateParameters) |
2455 RequiresInstanceMembersInitializer::encode(false) |
2456 HasBracesField::encode(has_braces) |
2457 ShouldParallelCompileField::encode(false);
2458 if (eager_compile_hint == kShouldEagerCompile) SetShouldEagerCompile();
2459 }
2460
2461 using FunctionSyntaxKindBits =
2462 Expression::NextBitField<FunctionSyntaxKind, 3>;
2463 using Pretenure = FunctionSyntaxKindBits::Next<bool, 1>;
2464 using HasDuplicateParameters = Pretenure::Next<bool, 1>;
2465 using RequiresInstanceMembersInitializer =
2466 HasDuplicateParameters::Next<bool, 1>;
2467 using HasStaticPrivateMethodsOrAccessorsField =
2468 RequiresInstanceMembersInitializer::Next<bool, 1>;
2469 using HasBracesField = HasStaticPrivateMethodsOrAccessorsField::Next<bool, 1>;
2470 using ShouldParallelCompileField = HasBracesField::Next<bool, 1>;
2471
2472 // expected_property_count_ is the sum of instance fields and properties.
2473 // It can vary depending on whether a function is lazily or eagerly parsed.
2474 int expected_property_count_;
2475 int parameter_count_;
2476 int function_length_;
2477 int function_token_position_;
2478 int suspend_count_;
2479 int function_literal_id_;
2480
2481 const AstConsString* raw_name_;
2482 DeclarationScope* scope_;
2483 ZonePtrList<Statement> body_;
2484 AstConsString* raw_inferred_name_;
2485 IndirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_function_info_;
2486 ProducedPreparseData* produced_preparse_data_;
2487};

2531// Property is used for passing information
2532// about a class literal's properties from the parser to the code generator.
2533class ClassLiteralProperty final : public LiteralProperty {
2534 public:
2535 enum Kind : uint8_t { METHOD, GETTER, SETTER, FIELD, AUTO_ACCESSOR };
2536
2537 Kind kind() const { return kind_; }
2538
2539 bool is_static() const { return is_static_; }
2540
2541 bool is_private() const { return is_private_; }
2542
2543 bool is_auto_accessor() const { return kind() == AUTO_ACCESSOR; }
2544
2545 void set_computed_name_proxy(VariableProxy* proxy) {
2546 DCHECK_EQ(FIELD, kind());
2547 DCHECK(!is_private());
2548 private_or_computed_name_proxy_ = proxy;
2549 }
2550
2551 Variable* computed_name_var() const {
2552 DCHECK_EQ(FIELD, kind());
2553 DCHECK(!is_private());
2554 return private_or_computed_name_proxy_->var();
2555 }
2556
2557 void SetPrivateNameProxy(VariableProxy* proxy) {
2558 DCHECK(is_private());
2559 if (is_auto_accessor()) {
2560 auto_accessor_info()->set_property_private_name_proxy(proxy);
2561 return;
2562 }
2563 private_or_computed_name_proxy_ = proxy;
2564 }
2565 Variable* private_name_var() const {
2566 DCHECK(is_private());
2567 DCHECK(!is_auto_accessor());
2568 return private_or_computed_name_proxy_->var();
2569 }
2570
2571 AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info() {
2572 DCHECK(is_auto_accessor());
2573 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(auto_accessor_info_);
2574 return auto_accessor_info_;
2575 }
2576
2577 private:
2578 friend class AstNodeFactory;
2579 friend Zone;
2580
2581 ClassLiteralProperty(Expression* key, Expression* value, Kind kind,
2582 bool is_static, bool is_computed_name, bool is_private);
2583 ClassLiteralProperty(Expression* key, Expression* value,
2584 AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info, bool is_static,
2585 bool is_computed_name, bool is_private);
2586
2587 Kind kind_;
2588 bool is_static_;
2589 bool is_private_;
2590 union {
2591 VariableProxy* private_or_computed_name_proxy_;
2592 AutoAccessorInfo* auto_accessor_info_;
2593 };
2594};

2917// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2918// Basic visitor
2919// Sub-class should parametrize AstVisitor with itself, e.g.:
2920// class SpecificVisitor : public AstVisitor<SpecificVisitor> { ... }
2921
2922template <class Subclass>
2923class AstVisitor {
2924 public:
2925 void Visit(AstNode* node) { impl()->Visit(node); }
2926
2927 void VisitDeclarations(Declaration::List* declarations) {
2928 for (Declaration* decl : *declarations) Visit(decl);
2929 }
2930
2931 void VisitStatements(const ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements) {
2932 for (int i = 0; i < statements->length(); i++) {
2933 Statement* stmt = statements->at(i);
2934 Visit(stmt);
2935 }
2936 }
2937
2938 void VisitExpressions(const ZonePtrList<Expression>* expressions) {
2939 for (int i = 0; i < expressions->length(); i++) {
2940 // The variable statement visiting code may pass null expressions
2941 // to this code. Maybe this should be handled by introducing an
2942 // undefined expression or literal? Revisit this code if this
2943 // changes.
2944 Expression* expression = expressions->at(i);
2945 if (expression != nullptr) Visit(expression);
2946 }
2947 }
2948
2949 protected:
2950 Subclass* impl() { return static_cast<Subclass*>(this); }
2951};
2952
2953#define GENERATE_VISIT_CASE(NodeType) \
2954 case AstNode::k##NodeType: \
2955 return this->impl()->Visit##NodeType(static_cast<NodeType*>(node));
2956
2957#define GENERATE_FAILURE_CASE(NodeType) \
2958 case AstNode::k##NodeType: \
2959 UNREACHABLE();
2960
2961#define GENERATE_AST_VISITOR_SWITCH() \
2962 switch (node->node_type()) { \
2963 AST_NODE_LIST(GENERATE_VISIT_CASE) \
2964 FAILURE_NODE_LIST(GENERATE_FAILURE_CASE) \
2965 }

2967#define DEFINE_AST_VISITOR_SUBCLASS_MEMBERS() \
2968 public: \
2969 void VisitNoStackOverflowCheck(AstNode* node) { \
2970 GENERATE_AST_VISITOR_SWITCH() \
2971 } \
2972 \
2973 void Visit(AstNode* node) { \
2974 if (CheckStackOverflow()) return; \
2975 VisitNoStackOverflowCheck(node); \
2976 } \
2977 \
2978 void SetStackOverflow() { stack_overflow_ = true; } \
2979 void ClearStackOverflow() { stack_overflow_ = false; } \
2980 bool HasStackOverflow() const { return stack_overflow_; } \
2981 \
2982 bool CheckStackOverflow() { \
2983 if (stack_overflow_) return true; \
2984 if (GetCurrentStackPosition() < stack_limit_) { \
2985 stack_overflow_ = true; \
2986 return true; \
2987 } \
2988 return false; \
2989 } \

2993 \

2997 stack_overflow_ = false; \
2998 } \

3002 stack_overflow_ = false; \

3184 class ThisExpression* ThisExpression() {
3185 // Clear any previously set "parenthesized" flag on this_expression_ so this
3186 // particular token does not inherit the it. The flag is used to check
3187 // during arrow function head parsing whether we came from parenthesized
3188 // exprssion parsing, since additional arrow function verification was done
3189 // there. It does not matter whether a flag is unset after arrow head
3190 // verification, so clearing at this point is fine.
3191 this_expression_->clear_parenthesized();
3192 return this_expression_;
3193 }

3404
3405 Assignment* NewAssignment(Token::Value op,
3406 Expression* target,
3407 Expression* value,
3408 int pos) {
3409 DCHECK(Token::IsAssignmentOp(op));
3410 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(target);
3411 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(value);
3412
3413 if (op != Token::kInit && target->IsVariableProxy()) {
3414 target->AsVariableProxy()->set_is_assigned();
3415 }
3416
3417 if (op == Token::kAssign || op == Token::kInit) {
3418 return zone_->New<Assignment>(AstNode::kAssignment, op, target, value,
3419 pos);
3420 } else {
3421 return zone_->New<CompoundAssignment>(
3422 op, target, value, pos,
3423 NewBinaryOperation(Token::BinaryOpForAssignment(op), target, value,
3424 pos + 1));
3425 }
3426 }

3609// Type testing & conversion functions overridden by concrete subclasses.
3610// Inline functions for AstNode.
3611
3612#define DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS(type) \
3613 bool AstNode::Is##type() const { return node_type() == AstNode::k##type; } \
3614 type* AstNode::As##type() { \
3615 return node_type() == AstNode::k##type ? reinterpret_cast<type*>(this) \
3616 : nullptr; \
3617 } \
3618 const type* AstNode::As##type() const { \
3619 return node_type() == AstNode::k##type \
3620 ? reinterpret_cast<const type*>(this) \
3621 : nullptr; \
3622 }
3623AST_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS)
3624FAILURE_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS)
3625#undef DECLARE_NODE_FUNCTIONS
